WEBVTT

00:00,000 --> 00:02,950
What actually improves modern l&d when teams are under pressure 03040500 sounds strategic, but the real constraint is operating behavior in the workflow.

00:03,000 --> 00:05,950
As output scales, decision clarity becomes the real bottleneck. Last week in the quarterly capability review, the blocker was not motivation.

00:06,000 --> 00:08,950
Problem one: teams collect more inputs, but weak checkpoints keep outcomes flat.

00:09,000 --> 00:11,950
So start with one owner, one metric, and one weekly review loop before scaling.

00:12,000 --> 00:14,950
Then ship in a short sprint so feedback stays close to live work.

00:15,000 --> 00:17,950
Problem two: once roles shift, old support models no longer fit live execution.

00:18,000 --> 00:20,950
So the strategic question is whether the system improves decisions or only produces artifacts.

00:21,000 --> 00:29,950
What do you think?
